    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in PDCCH PDU unpacking function\n\n### Summary\nThe function `unpack_dl_tti_pdcch_pdu_rel15_value()` in nr_fapi_p7.c was missing bounds checking on the `numDlDci` field, which could lead to buffer overflows when processing malformed data. This caused unexpected behavior including crashes and data corruption.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7.c`: Added bounds checking for `numDlDci`, `num_prgs`, and `dig_bf_interfaces` fields to prevent buffer overflows\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7.c`: Fixed typos in comments (\"Preocding\" -> \"Precoding\")\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `unpack_dl_tti_pdcch_pdu_rel15_value()` with a `numDlDci` value greater than `MAX_DCI_CORESET` (8), the function would access memory beyond the allocated `dci_pdu` array, causing segmentation faults or undefined behavior. Similar issues occurred with beamforming parameters exceeding their respective limits.\n\nThe fix adds proper bounds checking that validates input parameters before array access, returning an error code (0) and logging appropriate error messages when limits are exceeded.\n"
}